{#
  ============================================================================
  TEMPLATE: medicationstatement-eu-eps_fsh.twig
  ============================================================================
  PURPOSE
    Generates FSH instances for a patient's medication record conforming to
    the EU EPS profiles. Structurally identical to medicationstatement-eu-core_fsh.twig
    but targets different profiles and uses a slightly different data model
    for the medication code path and dosage handling.

  RELATIONSHIP TO medicationstatement-eu-core_fsh.twig
    Both templates implement the same two-mode pattern (no-medication sentinel
    vs full medication+statement pair). The key differences are:

    ┌──────────────────────────────┬──────────────────────┬──────────────────────────┐
    │ Aspect                       │ EU Core              │ EU EPS (this file)       │
    ├──────────────────────────────┼──────────────────────┼──────────────────────────┤
    │ MedicationStatement profile  │ MedicationStatementEuCore│ MedicationStatementEuEps │
    │ Medication SNOMED path       │ medication.code.code │ medication.snomed.code   │
    │ Medication text always set?  │ conditional          │ always (no if-guard)     │
    │ asNeeded handling            │ boolean + CC object  │ absent (not implemented) │
    │ contdose variable            │ present              │ absent                   │
    │ code.text[=] pattern         │ present              │ absent                   │
    │ Medication profile           │ MedicationEuCore     │ MedicationEuCore (same)  │
    └──────────────────────────────┴──────────────────────┴──────────────────────────┘

  PROFILE CONFORMANCE
    Mode A  MedicationStatement : MedicationStatementEuEps
    Mode B  Medication          : MedicationEuCore
            MedicationStatement : MedicationStatementEuEps

  TOP-LEVEL BRANCH PATTERN
    Identical to eu-core: entire %%FSH%% body wrapped in
    `{% if medication is empty %} … {% else %} … {% endif %}`.

  MODE A — NO KNOWN MEDICATIONS
    Identical to eu-core mode A except InstanceOf is MedicationStatementEuEps.

  MODE B — MEDICATION INSTANCE (first)
    SNOMED path is `medication.snomed.code` (not `medication.code.code`).
    `code.text` is always set to `medication.snomed.preferredTerm` without a
    conditional guard (unlike eu-core which uses `code.text[=]` conditionally).
    No `code.text[=]` pattern — the text rule uses plain `.text =` notation.

  MODE B — MEDICATION STATEMENT (second)
    Five-column HTML table: Medication | Since | Form | Dosage | Reason

    TD 1 — medication display name only; no `asNeeded` suffix logic.
    TD 2 — effectivePeriod.start (conditional; "-" if absent).
    TD 3 — dose form from `formdisplay` (same as eu-core).
    TD 4 — AI dosage injection (`medication.dosagefsh | raw`) followed by
            `medication.dosagedisplay` in HTML. No `contdose` variable —
            no subsequent asNeeded FSH rules to manage.
    TD 5 — clinical reason (`medication.reason.code`; SCT coding).

  CONTEXT VARIABLES
  ┌────────────────────────────────┬──────────┬────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
  │ Variable                       │ Type     │ Description                                    │
  ├────────────────────────────────┼──────────┼────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ instanceid                     │ string   │ Resource id for the MedicationStatement.       │
  │ druginstanceid                 │ string   │ Resource id for the Medication (Mode B only).  │
  │ patient.instanceid             │ string   │ UUID of the Patient resource.                  │
  │ patient.name                   │ string   │ Full display name.                             │
  │ medication                     │ object?  │ Empty → Mode A. Non-empty → Mode B.           │
  │   .snomed.code                 │ string?  │   SNOMED CT code (preferred over RxNorm).      │
  │   .snomed.display              │ string   │   SNOMED display text.                         │
  │   .snomed.preferredTerm        │ string   │   Preferred term; always set as code.text.     │
  │                                │          │   Must always be supplied.                     │
  │   .rxnorm.code                 │ string?  │   RxNorm code (used only when SNOMED absent).  │
  │   .rxnorm.display              │ string   │   RxNorm display text.                         │
  │   .start                       │ string?  │   ISO 8601 effectivePeriod start date.         │
  │   .dosagefsh                   │ string?  │   Pre-formatted FSH dosage string (AI-gen).    │
  │   .dosagedisplay               │ string?  │   Human-readable dosage for HTML td 4.         │
  │   .reason.code                 │ string?  │   SNOMED code for the clinical reason.         │
  │   .reason.display              │ string   │   Reason display text.                         │
  │ manufacturedDoseForm           │ object?  │   Dose form for Medication.form.coding.        │
  │   .code                        │ string   │   SNOMED CT code.                              │
  │   .display                     │ string   │   Display text (also stored in formdisplay).   │
  │ activeIngredient               │ object?  │   Active ingredient for ingredient[0].         │
  │   .code                        │ string   │   SNOMED CT code.                              │
  │   .display                     │ string   │   Ingredient display text.                     │
  └────────────────────────────────┴──────────┴────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

  CODESYSTEMS REFERENCED
    $sct    — SNOMED CT; medication code, dose form, ingredient, reason,
              "No known medications" (787481004)
    $rxnorm — RxNorm; fallback medication code when SNOMED absent

  AUTHOR   KH
  SINCE    2025-10-21
  ============================================================================
#}

%%FSH%% {# ── Section marker required by the FSH pre-processor ─────────────── #}

{% if medication is empty %}

{#
  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  MODE A — NO KNOWN MEDICATIONS
  Identical to eu-core variant except InstanceOf = MedicationStatementEuEps.
  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#}

Instance: {{ setInstance("Instance-MedicationStatement-" ~ instanceid) }}
InstanceOf: MedicationStatementEuEps
Title: "MedicationStatement"
Description: "MedicationStatement"
Usage: #inline
* id = "{{ instanceid }}"
* status = #active
* medicationCodeableConcept = $sct#787481004 "No known medications (situation)"
* subject = Reference(urn:uuid:{{ patient.instanceid }}) "{{ patient.name }}"
* effectivePeriod.extension.url = "http://hl7.org/fhir/StructureDefinition/data-absent-reason"
* effectivePeriod.extension.valueCode = #unknown
{{ addHTML_tr() }}
{{ addHTML_td("No known medications") }}
{{ addHTML_trend() -}}
* text.status = #generated
* text.div = """
<div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
<table class="hl7__ips first25">{{ emitHTML() | raw }}</table>
</div>
"""

{% else %}

{#
  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  MODE B — MEDICATION PRESENT
  Instance 1: Medication (MedicationEuCore)
  Instance 2: MedicationStatement (MedicationStatementEuEps)
  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#}

{#
  ── Instance 1: Medication ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
  SNOMED path differs from eu-core: medication.snomed.code (not medication.code.code).
  code.text is always set unconditionally to medication.snomed.preferredTerm.
  No code.text[=] pattern — plain text rule notation used.
#}
Instance: {{ setInstance("Instance-Medication-" ~ druginstanceid) }}
InstanceOf: MedicationEuCore
Title: "Medication"
Description: "Medication"
Usage: #inline

* id = "{{ druginstanceid }}"

{# SNOMED preferred; RxNorm fallback when SNOMED absent #}
{% if medication.snomed.code is not empty %}
* code.coding[+] = $sct#{{ medication.snomed.code }} "{{ medication.snomed.display }}"
{% else %}
{% if medication.rxnorm.code is not empty %}
* code.coding[+] = $rxnorm#{{ medication.rxnorm.code }} "{{ medication.rxnorm.display }}"
{% endif %}
{% endif %}
{# preferredTerm always set — no conditional guard, unlike eu-core #}
* code.text = "{{ medication.snomed.preferredTerm }}"

{#
  formdisplay — same pattern as eu-core: empty string or ", <display>"
  for reuse in Medication text.div and MedicationStatement HTML td 3.
#}
{% set formdisplay = "" %}
{% if manufacturedDoseForm.code is not empty %}
* form.coding = $sct#{{ manufacturedDoseForm.code }} "{{ manufacturedDoseForm.display }}"
{% set formdisplay = ", " ~ manufacturedDoseForm.display %}
{% endif %}

{% if activeIngredient.code is not empty %}
* ingredient[0].itemCodeableConcept = $sct#{{ activeIngredient.code }} "{{ activeIngredient.display }}"
* ingredient[0].isActive = true
{% endif %}

* text.status = #generated
* text.div = """
<div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
{{ medication.snomed.preferredTerm }} {{ formdisplay }}
</div>
"""

{#
  ── Instance 2: MedicationStatement ─────────────────────────────────────────
  Five-column table: Medication | Since | Form | Dosage | Reason
  Simpler than eu-core: no asNeeded logic, no contdose variable.
#}
Instance: {{ setInstance("Instance-MedicationStatement-" ~ instanceid) }}
InstanceOf: MedicationStatementEuEps
Title: "MedicationStatement"
Description: "MedicationStatement"
Usage: #inline

{{ addHEAD_tr() }}
{{ addHEAD_th("Medication") }}
{{ addHEAD_th("Since") }}
{{ addHEAD_th("Form") }}
{{ addHEAD_th("Dosage") }}
{{ addHEAD_th("Reason") }}
{{ addHEAD_trend() -}}

* id = "{{ instanceid }}"
* status = #active

{{ addHTML_tr() }}

{# TD 1: medication name — no asNeeded suffix in this EPS variant #}
* medicationReference = Reference(urn:uuid:{{ druginstanceid }}) "{{ medication.snomed.preferredTerm }}"
{{ addHTML_td(medication.snomed.preferredTerm) }}

* subject = Reference(urn:uuid:{{ patient.instanceid }}) "{{ patient.name }}"

{# TD 2: effective period start #}
{% if medication.start is not empty %}
* effectivePeriod.start = "{{ medication.start }}"
{{ addHTML_tdnb(medication.start) }}
{% else %}
{{ addHTML_td("-") }}
{% endif %}

{# TD 3: dose form #}
{% if formdisplay is not empty %}
{{ addHTML_td(formdisplay) }}
{% else %}
{{ addHTML_td("-") }}
{% endif %}

{#
  TD 4: AI dosage injection + display.
  No contdose management needed — no asNeeded rules follow the dosage block.
#}
{% if medication.dosagefsh is not empty %}
{{ medication.dosagefsh | raw }}
{{ addHTML_td(medication.dosagedisplay) }}
{% else %}
{{ addHTML_td("-") }}
{% endif %}

{# TD 5: clinical reason #}
{% if medication.reason.code is not empty %}
* reasonCode[0].coding = $sct#{{ medication.reason.code }} "{{ medication.reason.display }}"
{{ addHTML_td(medication.reason.display) }}
{% else %}
{{ addHTML_td("-") }}
{% endif %}

{{ addHTML_trend() -}}

* text.status = #generated
* text.div = """
<div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
<table class="hl7__ips first25">{{ emitHEAD() | raw }} {{ emitHTML() | raw }}</table>
</div>
"""

{% endif %} {# medication is empty / not empty #}

%%HEAD%% {# ── Section marker required by the FSH pre-processor ─────────────── #}
{{ emitHEAD() | raw }}

%%HTML%% {# ── Section marker required by the FSH pre-processor ─────────────── #}
{{ emitHTML() | raw }}
